  "why": "The paper provides diagnostic insight by linking discovered failures (adversarial and perturbed inputs) to model internals and statistical failure patterns: it models RNNs as an abstract DTMC, defines state- and transition-based trace similarity, and shows empirically that (1) trace-similarity correlates with prediction differences and (2) adversarial/perturbed samples tend to exercise rarely-visited states/transitions (coverage changes). These analyses connect failures to internal behavior (state / transition frequencies and trace divergence), but the paper does not trace failures back to deeper root causes such as corrupted or biased training data, spurious input features, or overfitting; hence it gives partial (internal/statistical) diagnostics rather than full root-cause explanations.",
